7699        /// Returns the signature for the given selector, if known.
7700        #[inline]
7701        pub fn signature_by_selector(
7702            selector: [u8; 4usize],
7703        ) -> ::core::option::Option<&'static str> {
7704            match Self::SELECTORS.binary_search(&selector) {
7705                ::core::result::Result::Ok(idx) => {
7706                    ::core::option::Option::Some(Self::SIGNATURES[idx])
7707                }
7708                ::core::result::Result::Err(_) => ::core::option::Option::None,
7709            }
7710        }
7711        /// Returns the enum variant name for the given selector, if known.
7712        #[inline]
7713        pub fn name_by_selector(
7714            selector: [u8; 4usize],
7715        ) -> ::core::option::Option<&'static str> {
7716            let sig = Self::signature_by_selector(selector)?;
7717            sig.split_once('(').map(|(name, _)| name)
7718        }
7719    }

9210
9211Returns a new instance of the contract, if the deployment was successful.
9212
9213For more fine-grained control over the deployment process, use [`deploy_builder`] instead.*/
9214        #[inline]
9215        pub async fn deploy(
9216            __provider: P,
9217            newAdmin: alloy::sol_types::private::Address,
9218            baseTokenURI: alloy::sol_types::private::String,
9219        ) -> alloy_contract::Result<HoprBoostInstance<P, N>> {
9220            let call_builder = Self::deploy_builder(__provider, newAdmin, baseTokenURI);

9222            Ok(Self::new(contract_address, call_builder.provider))
9223        }
9224        /**Creates a `RawCallBuilder` for deploying this contract using the given `provider`
9225and constructor arguments, if any.
9226
9227This is a simple wrapper around creating a `RawCallBuilder` with the data set to
9228the bytecode concatenated with the constructor's ABI-encoded arguments.*/
9229        #[inline]
9230        pub fn deploy_builder(

9232            newAdmin: alloy::sol_types::private::Address,
9233            baseTokenURI: alloy::sol_types::private::String,
9234        ) -> alloy_contract::RawCallBuilder<P, N> {
9235            alloy_contract::RawCallBuilder::new_raw_deploy(
9236                __provider,
9237                [
9238                    &BYTECODE[..],
9239                    &alloy_sol_types::SolConstructor::abi_encode(
9240                        &constructorCall {
9241                            newAdmin,
9242                            baseTokenURI,
9243                        },
9244                    )[..],
9245                ]
9246                    .concat()
9247                    .into(),
9248            )
9249        }

9282    /// Function calls.
9283    impl<
9284        P: alloy_contract::private::Provider<N>,
9285        N: alloy_contract::private::Network,
9286    > HoprBoostInstance<P, N> {
9287        /// Creates a new call builder using this contract instance's provider and address.
9288        ///
9289        /// Note that the call can be any function call, not just those defined in this
9290        /// contract. Prefer using the other methods for building type-safe contract calls.
9291        pub fn call_builder<C: alloy_sol_types::SolCall>(
9292            &self,
9293            call: &C,
9294        ) -> alloy_contract::SolCallBuilder<&P, C, N> {
9295            alloy_contract::SolCallBuilder::new_sol(&self.provider, &self.address, call)
9296        }
9297        ///Creates a new call builder for the [`DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE`] function.
9298        pub fn DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE(

9615    /// Event filters.
9616    impl<
9617        P: alloy_contract::private::Provider<N>,
9618        N: alloy_contract::private::Network,
9619    > HoprBoostInstance<P, N> {
9620        /// Creates a new event filter using this contract instance's provider and address.
9621        ///
9622        /// Note that the type can be any event, not just those defined in this contract.
9623        /// Prefer using the other methods for building type-safe event filters.
9624        pub fn event_filter<E: alloy_sol_types::SolEvent>(
9625            &self,
9626        ) -> alloy_contract::Event<&P, E, N> {
9627            alloy_contract::Event::new_sol(&self.provider, &self.address)
9628        }
9629        ///Creates a new event filter for the [`Approval`] event.
9630        pub fn Approval_filter(&self) -> alloy_contract::Event<&P, Approval, N> {
9631            self.event_filter::<Approval>()
9632        }
9633        ///Creates a new event filter for the [`ApprovalForAll`] event.
9634        pub fn ApprovalForAll_filter(
9635            &self,
9636        ) -> alloy_contract::Event<&P, ApprovalForAll, N> {
9637            self.event_filter::<ApprovalForAll>()
9638        }
9639        ///Creates a new event filter for the [`BoostMinted`] event.
9640        pub fn BoostMinted_filter(&self) -> alloy_contract::Event<&P, BoostMinted, N> {
9641            self.event_filter::<BoostMinted>()
9642        }
9643        ///Creates a new event filter for the [`RoleAdminChanged`] event.
9644        pub fn RoleAdminChanged_filter(
9645            &self,
9646        ) -> alloy_contract::Event<&P, RoleAdminChanged, N> {
9647            self.event_filter::<RoleAdminChanged>()
9648        }
9649        ///Creates a new event filter for the [`RoleGranted`] event.
